I have a PR against 23.01 failed with mypy type checking on lines I didn't touch in CI. Has anyone seen similar issue when backporting fixes against this branch before?
https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/55071

`[TOTAL]: 130  [OK]:95  [FAIL]:35` - it seems like mypy failed in 35 modules :thinking_rotating:
Some errors:
```12:09:35  instabase_unit_tests/instabase/license_utils/test_utils.py: error: Source file found twice under different module names: 'py.instabase_unit_tests.instabase.license_utils.test_utils' and 'instabase_unit_tests.instabase.license_utils.test_utils'```
```12:21:23  TYPECHECKING FAILURE: mypy exited with code 1
12:21:23  instabase_unit_tests/instabase/utils/oauth2/test_ib_jwt_auth.py:72: error: Argument 2 has incompatible type "bytes"; expected "str"

12:21:23  instabase_unit_tests/instabase/utils/oauth2/test_ib_jwt_auth.py:110: error: Argument 2 has incompatible type "bytes"; expected "str"

@sean.donohoe I remember some PRs were put up to resolve a lot of mypy errors across the code base when the mypy version got bumped. Did the cherry-pick not make it to 23.01 (and likely 22.10)?
@Anil was the py version bump to 3.9 in mypy configs backported to 23.01?
@Heymian iirc 23.01/22.10 didn't need to a cp because they were still utilizing mypy 0.701 :thinking_face:
Yeah, I just had deja vu because that was also my vague recollection too when we talked about the cherry-picks for those changes.
I do remember some mypy changes a while back that I think @youngmok.cho is referencing, those sound like the most likely cause but I'm digging around for anything else
